  <section class="article-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">About</p><h1>About Offline Maps Guide</h1><p>Practical research for travelers who need navigation to keep working without a signal.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container article"><h2>What we publish</h2><p>Offline Maps Guide covers offline navigation apps, downloadable map workflows, storage planning, privacy tradeoffs, and trip-specific preparation for international travel, hiking, and road trips.</p><h2>How we research</h2><p>We prioritize official app documentation, platform listings, clearly dated product information, and reproducible setup steps. The methodology and editorial-policy pages explain how volatile app features and claims are reviewed.</p><h2>Independent status</h2><p>Offline Maps Guide is independently operated and is not affiliated with Google, Apple, Organic Maps, OsmAnd, Kiwix, or other products mentioned in its guides.</p></div></section>
